summary:
Serum ferritin is the most sensitive test for detecting iron depletion in pregnancy because it directly reflects stored iron and decreases before clinically significant changes occur. It surpasses other markers such as serum iron, transferrin, or total iron-binding capacity due to its ability to identify early deficiencies prior to hematological alterations. \boxed{B}

