Final Summary:

Serum ferritin is the most sensitive test for detecting iron depletion in pregnancy because it directly indicates available iron stores and diminishes first in deficiency. Though inflamed tissues may elevate ferritin falsely, it remains preferable to serum iron, transferrin, or TIBC for timely diagnosis of early iron insufficiency. \boxed{B}
